1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,500
Beloved Pastor, and Pastors amongst us, and sisters and brothers, God bless you all.

2
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:09,500
大兄姊妹各位的神賜福給你

3
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:14,000
Let's bow our heads and pray together.

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:17,000
讓我們一起祈禱

5
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Lord, we give you thanks for this time that you have made for us.

6
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:24,500
我們向你獻上感恩,有這個時間

7
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:27,000
We want to hear your voice.

8
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,000
我們盼望聽到你自己的聲音

9
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:33,000
We ask that you grant us a listening ear and obedient heart.

10
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:38,000
我求你給到我們一雙聆聽的耳朵和一個順服的心

11
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,000
In Jesus' name we pray.

12
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,000
奉主耶穌的聖名去祈求

13
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,000
Amen

14
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Again, it's a delight to be coming to this familiar place.

15
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,000
來到這個很相熟的地方實在是很高興

16
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Many years ago, a very well-intentioned and elderly sisters

17
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:01,000
came to me and posed a question to my throat.

18
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:06,000
很多年前,有一個很有善意的年老姊妹問了我一個問題

19
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:10,000
He said, "Dennis, you have preached many sermons on love."

20
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Dennis,你講過很多有關愛的講道,對不對?

21
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:17,000
May I ask you a very simple question?

22
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,000
我想問一個很簡單的問題

23
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Is your life an interpretation of love?

24
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:25,000
你的生命是否一個愛的詮釋呢?

25
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:28,000
She didn't mean to be mean to me.

26
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:31,000
She's a very loving sister and mother.

27
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:35,000
她是一個很有愛的媽媽,是一個很有愛的姊妹

28
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,000
她不是特別挑剔我的

29
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Yes,挑剔我, beautiful translation.

30
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:45,000
She came to me and asked, "Is your life an interpretation of love?"

31
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:49,000
她就來到我那裡問,究竟你的生命本身是否一個愛的詮釋呢?

32
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:52,000
Is your life an illustration of love?

33
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:55,000
你的生命是否一個愛的例子呢?

34
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:59,000
Is your life a concrete example of love?

35
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:02,000
你的生命有沒有表彰到愛呢?

36
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:07,000
When people look at you, there is no speculations, no suspicions.

37
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:13,000
Crystal clear. This person, this person, that person is an interpretation of love.

38
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:24,000
是否每個人走過來看,沒有任何的猜測,沒有任何的懷疑,就很清楚在你的生命看到究竟真愛是甚麼?

39
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:27,000
You see, it's so easy to sing love song.

40
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:30,000
其實唱一首愛情的歌都很容易

41
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:33,000
It's very easy to preach a sermon on love.

42
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,000
或者講有愛的講道都不是很難

43
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:39,000
Yes, I have preached many sermons on love.

44
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:43,000
我講過愛的講道有很多的了

45
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:47,000
But I thought a lot about her questions, is your life an interpretation of love?

46
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:53,000
但是我真是想她的問題想了很久,究竟我的生命是否一個愛的詮釋呢?

47
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:58,000
You see, love is better, some people put it this way, love is better felt than tell.

48
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:03,000
有人會這樣說,愛是更好被感受而不是被言說

49
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:10,000
And love is better interpreted than instructed.

50
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:18,000
And love is better demonstrated than defined.

51
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:23,000
You see, Saint Paul is a giant of faith.

52
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:27,000
A mighty thinker that he was.

53
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:35,000
He was not a man with nothing between the ears.

54
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:43,000
對,他很聰明,他的腦袋很聰明。

55
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:50,000
A mighty thinker,不是腦袋空空的。

56
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:57,000
And Paul not only talked about love, 1 Corinthians 13,

57
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:03,000
but here he illustrated love in the most vivid way, in the way he treated his co-worker.

58
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:10,000
但當我們看到他怎樣去對待他的同工的時候,我們就真真正正看到他怎樣展示出愛。

59
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:15,000
The historical context of the book,

60
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:24,000
There are three major characters, Philemon, the master of Anasimus,

61
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:29,000
And Anasimus is the runaway slave.

62
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:36,000
And Saint Paul, the common pastor or common mentor.

63
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:44,000
You see, Anasimus was guilty of stealing from his master Philemon.

64
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:47,000
So he was a runaway slave.

65
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:55,000
And through the ministry of Saint Paul, his life was deeply changed and became a Christian.

66
00:04:55,000 --> 00:05:04,000
According to Roman law, slaves must be returned to their masters.

67
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:14,000
So he was about to send him back to Philemon.

68
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:20,000
And there he wrote this beautiful letter to Philemon.

69
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:29,000
It's a very small letter, but filled with great affections and love.

70
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:43,000
And today is Mother's Day, let me share with you how you and I could be an interpreter of love.

71
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:48,000
Yes, three point sermon.

72
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:50,000
Three point, point number one.

73
00:05:50,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Love is interpreted not in commanding, but in respecting each other.

74
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:12,000
You see, Paul, an older man, a godly man, a man filled with authority.

75
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:29,000
You see, a godly man, he had the authority to command Philemon to receive back Anasimus.

76
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:46,000
Instead, he wrote a letter not commanding him what he should do, but what? Appealing on the basis of love.

77
00:06:46,000 --> 00:07:07,000
You see, not commanding what he should do, not threatening, not warning, not imposing, not demanding what Philemon ought to do with the runaway slaves.

78
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:14,000
And yet, he wrote the letter appealing on the basis of love.

79
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:22,000
In verse number nine, Paul said, "I appeal to you on the basis of love."

80
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:35,000
You see, not on the basis of authority which he possessed, but now he appealed on the basis of love.

81
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:41,000
You see, "I appeal for my spiritual son, Anasimus."

82
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:46,000
You see, here I learned something.

83
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:57,000
Did you see how sensitive that Paul was towards his colleague?

84
00:07:57,000 --> 00:08:10,000
He merely made a humble request on behalf of the runaway slave.

85
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:17,000
And he left the final decision to Philemon himself.

86
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:24,000
Is it not love truly manifest and interpreted?

87
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:40,000
He showed respect to him.You see, authority is very important to leadership.

88
00:08:40,000 --> 00:09:01,000
We, company presidents, pastors, parents, we are all given authority to rule.You see, but authority must be upheld in decency.

89
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:11,000
It must be held in modesty.

90
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:21,000
And also, it must be exercised with love and affection.

91
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:34,000
Because authority in itself is not evil, but it can become evil because of the abuse and the misuse of it.

92
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:40,000
And there are people who abuse the authority.

93
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:49,000
There are people who have to command because they simply cannot trust others.

94
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:56,000
There are people who demand because they think they are indispensable.

95
00:09:56,000 --> 00:10:01,000
They think that they are irreplaceable.

96
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:10,000
And therefore, they can say anything they want without considering the feelings of others into account.

97
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:22,000
And others enjoy and command because they are so afraid of losing power and losing control.

98
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:28,000
You see, let me apply it to the family context.

99
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:44,000
You see, a highly chauvinistic husband, after one week of marriage, he came to the pastor who officiated the wedding.

100
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:52,000
And he said, "Pastor, last week your sermon was so good."

101
00:10:52,000 --> 00:11:00,000
You said when two of us got married, the two became one.

102
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:06,000
But pastor, you never told me which one.

103
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:12,000
Do you understand what he is saying?

104
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:19,000
Is it my body throw her until death do us part?

105
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:29,000
Is it her body join with me so that she could nag, nag, nag, nag until death do us part?

106
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:42,000
You see, this is premarital counseling for many of young people, but post-marital counseling.

107
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:53,000
You see, some of you men, you try and command your wife and see what will happen.

108
00:11:53,000 --> 00:12:06,000
Some of you women, you try and order your husband around, I can guarantee you your better half will become the bitter half.

109
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:13,000
The first two years of my marriage was hellish.

110
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:24,000
Why? Because we try to change each other.

111
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:30,000
I try to change her into my likeness.

112
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:36,000
And she try to change me into her likeness.

113
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:40,000
But both of us are unlike Christ.

114
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:53,000
How can you change your spouse into your likeness when you have no Christ likeness?

115
00:12:53,000 --> 00:13:03,000
You see, in Chinese, he wants to change me into his likeness.

116
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:09,000
He wants to change me into his likeness.

117
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:15,000
She wants to change me, I want to change her.

118
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:23,000
But we are not the same.I don't know what she said.

119
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:25,000
You don't like each other.

120
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:27,000
No, no, no, no, no, no.

121
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:29,000
就是不像.

122
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:33,000
她選我,像她,但她自己都不像.

123
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:38,000
Oh, she wants me to look like her, but she doesn't look like Christ.

124
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:49,000
The problem is we try to change each other, you can change each other unless you are Christ-like.

125
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:57,000
And then later on, God convicted both of us.

126
00:13:57,000 --> 00:14:04,000
You see, and cause us to kneel before God and repent.

127
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:17,000
And we learn to respect each other and treat one another as God's gift.

128
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:27,000
You see, it is not my job to change my spouse.

129
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:33,000
It is God's job.

130
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:49,000
We kneel before God and asking God to change us for the sake of another, for the sake of her.

131
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:57,000
You see, brothers and sisters, we must learn to let go of our self-centeredness.

132
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:02,000
We must learn to respect others.

133
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:11,000
We often say respect must be earned.

134
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:18,000
But may I add, respect must be learned.

135
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:27,000
See, respect must be learned and in the process of learning, you earn it.

136
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:39,000
We can only learn respect by seeking to esteem others above ourselves.

137
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:47,000
You see, Paul learned to be respectful towards Philemon.

138
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:56,000
You see, in verse 14, he said, "I did not want to do anything without your consent."

139
00:15:56,000 --> 00:16:06,000
So that any favor you do will be spontaneous and not forced.

140
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:18,000
So we must learn, learn. In the process of learning, we gain the respect.

141
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:30,000
You see, one of the great philosophers by the name of Cheeky Chesterton once made a very, very catching phrase.

142
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:35,000
He said, "Why do angels fly?

143
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:44,000
Why do angels fly and then fly higher and freer and joyfully?"

144
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:58,000
Oh, his answer was brilliant. "Why do angels fly? Because they take themselves lightly."

145
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:08,000
You see, our problem is we take ourselves too weightily. We put too much weight on ourselves.

146
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:16,000
Therefore, we cannot fly higher. We become clumsier than ever.

147
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:26,000
You see, we put too much weight on ourselves. We have to be on diet.

148
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:46,000
I used to put a lot of weight on myself. I put too much weight on myself. And then later on, I was on diet.

149
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:59,000
當我們把自己的位置放得很重很重要的時候,我們就會很亂七八糟。

150
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:07,000
為什麼要看自己這麼重?有意思嗎?有意思嗎?

151
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:17,000
You see, we must learn not to put too much weight on ourselves.

152
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:25,000
I have been on diet. Therefore, I look much better than before.

153
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:45,000
I can be natural and free and be myself. See, translation is very good.

154
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:51,000
人家說三自教會,我也是三自。自然,自由,自在。

155
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:56,000
I can be natural. I can be free. I can be without pretense.

156
00:18:56,000 --> 00:19:08,000
Second point, love is interpreted not in depreciating others but making others useful.

157
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:14,000
To encourage others so that others may be built up.

158
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:36,000
I was captured by verse number 11. Formally, oneness was useless but now he has become both useful to me and to you and to me.

159
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:44,000
You see, what a sharp contrast between what formerly but now.

160
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:53,000
What a transformation from being useless to being useful.

161
00:19:53,000 --> 00:20:01,000
It takes a long time to make somebody useful.

162
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:14,000
It takes a lot of patience and strenuous activities and time to make others stand tall.

163
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:31,000
You see, tradition said Paul had made this person into a bishop.

164
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:39,000
You see, Onesimus later became an influential bishop of Asia Minor Church.

165
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:44,000
So brothers and sisters, why are you still here?

166
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:57,000
Is it because of the efforts of mothers and mentors and pastors?

167
00:20:57,000 --> 00:21:02,000
Today is Mother's Day. I must talk about my mom.

168
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:05,000
Are you ready to hear?

169
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:20,000
My mom said whenever you miss me, you put on a tie, either a pink tie or a tie with pink color on it.

170
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:27,000
Then the tie brings the two hearts together.

171
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:37,000
Because of this tie, heaven and earth are breached.

172
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:41,000
My mother used to advise me this.

173
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:57,000
Son, if you want a lot of followers, you have a lot of pupils on earth.

174
00:21:57,000 --> 00:22:06,000
You see, if you want to have a lot of followers, I pray that God will give you two things.

175
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:15,000
May God give you a penetrating eye and a compassionate heart.

176
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:36,000
With the two things combined, you would be a very effective agent of love.

177
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:47,000
Your eyes are beautiful, but good for nothing.You are so blind to the people's struggle.

178
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:55,000
You see, you are blind to the disappointments that people feel.

179
00:22:55,000 --> 00:23:03,000
Sometimes your hearts do not have feeling towards those people who fail.

180
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:12,000
I ask God daily that God will give you a penetrating eye.

181
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:21,000
You see, to see what goes on inside the heart of others.

182
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:33,000
And to ask God for a heart that feels the hurt of others.

183
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:42,000
And only then you will be the best illustration of love.

184
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:49,000
You see, how do you develop a penetrating eye?

185
00:23:49,000 --> 00:24:00,000
The song that you just sing, the song, I love to hear your voice.

186
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:12,000
In order to have a penetrating eye, you must hear the word of God, God's voice.

187
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:22,000
But also you must listen to the voices of godly leaders and mentors above you.

188
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:27,000
I was thankful for my mother.

189
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:33,000
You see, because of her, I was no longer the same.

190
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:38,000
You see, I am indebted to my mother.

191
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:45,000
I am sure you have a lot of story to tell about your mother.

192
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:53,000
You see, I am indebted to her in terms of my beauty.

193
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:58,000
My mother give it to me.

194
00:24:58,000 --> 00:25:05,000
So any beauty that I have, I give it back to my mother.

195
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:14,000
And any virtue that I possess, I give it back to my mother.

196
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:21,000
Not just the beauty, but also virtues.

197
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:25,000
I give it back to my mother.

198
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:38,000
You see, credit be given to my mother who labor to make me beautiful and make me virtuous.

199
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:44,000
Glory be to God.

200
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:54,000
Glory be to God, credit be given to my mother who make me beautiful, make me virtuous.

201
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:59,000
But you must not forget the third point.

202
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:02,000
Labor be given to me.

203
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:07,000
Labor, hard work, hard work.

204
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:10,000
要下功夫。

205
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:14,000
功勞是給我爸,功夫是給我自己。

206
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:17,000
功勞就給我媽媽。

207
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:20,000
I have made the hard effort.

208
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:22,000
Is that right?

209
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:27,000
You have to do something, right?

210
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:30,000
And you appreciate your mom.

211
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:36,000
Because God has given her to you.

212
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:51,000
So I am continuing learning and growing in being penetrating in my eyes, compassionate in my heart.

213
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:59,000
So may God restore our sight and inflame our hearts.

214
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:01,000
The third point.

215
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:13,000
Love is interpreted not in being calculative, but being magnanimous, being generous.

216
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:16,000
You see, there are two kinds of people.

217
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:20,000
Big people and little people.

218
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:25,000
Little people have little heart.

219
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:31,000
Little people have little heart.

220
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:35,000
Big people have big heart.

221
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:38,000
Little people have little heart.

222
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:47,000
The heart is so small that it contains nobody but himself.

223
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:52,000
And such a person has very little influence.

224
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:56,000
Because he can't see anything but himself.

225
00:27:56,000 --> 00:28:00,000
But big people have big heart.

226
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:03,000
Or a generosity of spirit.

227
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:11,000
You see, the English word magnanimity, magnanimity of heart.

228
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:18,000
The heart big enough to take in the mistakes of others.

229
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:24,000
And it could conclude the past failures of others.

230
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:30,000
The differences in personality.

231
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:35,000
You see, Paul could have calculated.

232
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:48,000
He could ask himself how can I associate with somebody like Onesimus who had a criminal record.

233
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:55,000
You see, that will be a threat to my image as the leader.

234
00:28:55,000 --> 00:29:06,000
It could be a very, very big inconvenience to the development of my image as the leader.

235
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:12,000
You see, Paul manifests a big heart.

236
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:26,000
You see, in verse number 12, did you see how he addressed Onesimus, the criminal? My very heart.

237
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:30,000
You see,我的心上人,我的心肛.

238
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:39,000
In verse 16, he regarded him better than a slave.

239
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:46,000
And he is very dear to me, dearer, even dearer to you, both as a partner, as a brother in Christ.

240
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:53,000
他又繼續講,佢係我親愛嘅,佢亦都係你親愛嘅。佢係我哋嘅同伴,佢係我哋嘅弟兄。

241
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:57,000
And in verse 18, he said, if he owed you anything, charge it to me.

242
00:29:57,000 --> 00:30:04,000
喺第十八節,佢話,如果佢有乜嘢規範你嘅,欠你啲乜嘢嘅,你就算喺我嘅頭上啦。

243
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:09,000
You see, the word "charge" has to do with the gospel of justification.

244
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:15,000
其實個個"charge"呢個字係代表"算在"或者"充當"係講一個清義嘅複音。

245
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:16,000
"規制"

246
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:18,000
或者"規" -- to charge.

247
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:25,000
You see, "charge" has -- so Augustine spoke about the joyousest change between Christ's righteousness and our sin.

248
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:31,000
阿古斯丁咁樣講,佢話喺基督嘅義同埋我哋中間有個喜樂嘅交換。

249
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:37,000
We do not have our own righteousness to stand before God.

250
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:41,000
We are absolutely bankrupt.

251
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:48,000
But Christ's righteousness is given to us.

252
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:55,000
By His righteousness, I am right with God.

253
00:30:55,000 --> 00:31:03,000
You see, the righteousness is credited, it's reckoned, it's charged into me.

254
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:11,000
So that by His righteousness, we are made right with God.

255
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:18,000
See, Onesimus was indebted to his master and cannot pay back.

256
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:23,000
He has no money in his bank to pay back the master.

257
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:32,000
So Paul literally paid in order to purchase his freedom.

258
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:35,000
Is that not the gospel?

259
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:38,000
We as sinners, we are in debt.

260
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:47,000
We have nothing in our bank account to pay anything.

261
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:53,000
Christ stepped in to pay the debt of sin so that we may be set free.

262
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:59,000
大主耶穌基督就落到嚟世間上面,站喺上帝同人中間,為我哋還清一切。

263
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:07,000
So having been touched by the generosity of the gospel, now he applied in the way he dealt with this runaway slave.

264
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:13,000
當保羅自己親自領受過,親自被福音呢個義去觸動過嘅時候,

265
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:19,000
佢就將喺亞利西姆身上做返同一件事。

266
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:22,000
佢就話將佢嘅債算喺我嘅頭上。

267
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:24,000
我會還嘅。

268
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:29,000
So he is given back, he is given the total freedom back to the Philemon's household.

269
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:35,000
所以佢將呢個自由就畀返佢嘅家嗰度。

270
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:39,000
Did you experience the gospel?

271
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:42,000
Have you been forgiven?

272
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:46,000
And because we are forgiven, we ought to be forgiving.

273
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:52,000
因為我哋係被寬恕,被原諒,我哋都需要去原諒同埋去寬恕別人。

274
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:58,000
Because we are God's beloved creatures, we must be most loving of all creatures.

275
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:07,000
因為我哋係神自己嘅創造物,我哋有佢嘅愛,我哋必須用愛。

276
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:12,000
我們是被愛的。

277
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:18,000
And we become the beloved people of God.

278
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:22,000
You see,我們變成可愛嘅人。

279
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:28,000
Cute people, so therefore we need to be cute towards others.

280
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:33,000
And you don't curse people, you become cute towards others.

281
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:37,000
你唔係去貶低人,唔係去話人,但係我哋對人係好可愛嘅。

282
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:45,000
See, in this Mother's Day, I know there are many mixed feelings amongst mothers and amongst those people who are not mothers.

283
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:49,000
或者喺個母親節,可能大家有唔同嘅感受。

284
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:54,000
We may have differences amongst each one of us, amongst us in our family.

285
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:58,000
或者我哋, even 喺個家庭入面,我哋會有好多嘅唔同。

286
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:00,000
We may have misunderstanding.

287
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:10,000
讓我哋一齊學習點樣將呢啲誤解誤會擺開。

288
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:12,000
And learn to forgive others.

289
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:15,000
我哋一齊去學習點樣去寬恕別人。

290
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:17,000
And let us not be calculative.

291
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:20,000
冇去計較。

292
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:23,000
Manifest a magnanimous heart to each other.

293
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:26,000
去展示出一個咁偉大嘅愛究竟係點樣。

294
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:33,000
And you may say to yourself, "I cannot forgive."

295
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:41,000
If that's the case, let me share with you the words of Charles Burton.

296
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:47,000
He said, "Let us go to the cross."

297
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:56,000
Let us go to the cross and learn how we are forgiven.

298
00:34:56,000 --> 00:35:00,000
And let us stay there, linger, linger, stay there long enough

299
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:12,000
so that you know how you may forgive others.

300
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:20,000
Or we need to go beneath the cross and stay there a bit longer.

301
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:28,000
And from there you will have a bigness of heart.

302
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:32,000
Because the bigness of heart flows from the heart of God,

303
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:45,000
from those who are touched by the big and omnipotent, almighty love of God.

304
00:35:45,000 --> 00:36:06,000
Let us pray.

305
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:22,000
And give to each one of us the grace of forgiveness.

306
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:25,000
In Jesus name we pray.

307
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:26,000
Amen.

